&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>PuppetDB&lt;sup id="fnref:1">&lt;a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1&lt;/a>&lt;/sup> allows you to retrieve data collected by &lt;a href="./puppet_:_solution_de_gestion_de_fichier_de_configuration.html">Puppet&lt;/a> such as facts and to use exported resources among other things. This data can then be used by other programs, such as the &lt;a href="./Puppet_Dashboard_:_Mise_en_place_d'une_interface_graphique_pour_Puppet.html">dashboard&lt;/a>, or your own tools through an API. You can install the PuppetDB server on your PuppetMaster or on a separate server.&lt;sup id="fnref:2">&lt;a href="#fn:2" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">2&lt;/a>&lt;/sup>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>